name: add
desc: add a single annotation to the map

name: addAll
desc:
Adds a multiple annotations to the map. This much faster than calling add
multiple times

name: allLayerProperties
desc: implemented to define the layer properties

name: byId
desc: get the an annotation by its id

name: clear
desc: Removes all annotations from the map

name: dispose
desc:
Fully dipose of all the the resouces managed by the annotation manager.
The manager cannot be used after this has been called

name: enableInteraction
desc: If disabled the manager offers no interaction for the created symbols

name: id
desc: base id of the manager. User layerdIds to get the actual ids.

name: onTap
desc: Called if a annotation is tapped

name: remove
desc: Remove a single annotation form the map

name: removeAll
desc: Removes multiple annotations from the map

name: selectLayer
desc:
used to spedicy the layer and annotation will life on
This can be replaced by layer filters a soon as they are implemented

name: set
desc:
Set an existing anntotation to the map. Use this to do a fast update for a
single annotation

name: values
desc: A constant List of the values in this enum, in order of their declaration.

name: circleBlur
desc:
Amount to blur the circle. 1 blurs the circle such that only the
centerpoint is full opacity.

name: circleColor
desc: The fill color of the circle.

name: circleOpacity
desc: The opacity at which the circle will be drawn.

name: circlePitchAlignment
desc: Orientation of circle when map is pitched.

name: circlePitchScale
desc: Controls the scaling behavior of the circle when the map is pitched.

name: circleRadius
desc: Circle radius.

name: circleSortKey
desc:
Sorts features in ascending order based on this value. Features with a
higher sort key will appear above features with a lower sort key.

name: circleStrokeColor
desc: The stroke color of the circle.

name: circleStrokeOpacity
desc: The opacity of the circle's stroke.

name: circleStrokeWidth
desc:
The width of the circle's stroke. Strokes are placed outside of the
circle-radius.

name: circleTranslate
desc:
The geometry's offset. Values are x, y where negatives indicate left
and up, respectively.

name: circleTranslateAnchor
desc: Controls the frame of reference for circle-translate.

name: visibility
desc: Whether this layer is displayed.

name: allLayerProperties
desc: implemented to define the layer properties

name: values
desc: A constant List of the values in this enum, in order of their declaration.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: abs
desc: Returns the absolute value of the input.

name: accumulated
desc:
Gets the value of a cluster property accumulated so far. Can only be
used in the clusterProperties option of a clustered GeoJSON source.

name: acos
desc: Returns the arccosine of the input.

name: all
desc:
Returns true if all the inputs are true, false otherwise. The
inputs are evaluated in order, and evaluation is short-circuiting:
once an input expression evaluates to false, the result is false
and no further input expressions are evaluated.

name: any
desc:
Returns true if any of the inputs are true, false otherwise. The
inputs are evaluated in order, and evaluation is short-circuiting:
once an input expression evaluates to true, the result is true and
no further input expressions are evaluated.

name: array
desc:
Asserts that the input is an array (optionally with a specific item
type and length).  If, when the input expression is evaluated, it is
not of the asserted type, then this assertion will cause the whole
expression to be aborted.

name: asin
desc: Returns the arcsine of the input.

name: at
desc: Retrieves an item from an array.

name: atan
desc: Returns the arctangent of the input.

name: boolean
desc:
Asserts that the input value is a boolean. If multiple values are
provided, each one is evaluated in order until a boolean is obtained.
If none of the inputs are booleans, the expression is an error.

name: caseExpression
desc:
Selects the first output whose corresponding test condition evaluates
to true, or the fallback value otherwise.

name: ceil
desc:
Returns the smallest integer that is greater than or equal to the
input.

name: coalesce
desc:
Evaluates each expression in turn until the first non-null value is
obtained, and returns that value.

name: collator
desc:
Returns a collator for use in locale-dependent comparison
operations. The case-sensitive and diacritic-sensitive options
default to false. The locale argument specifies the IETF language
tag of the locale to use. If none is provided, the default locale is
used. If the requested locale is not available, the collator will
use a system-defined fallback locale. Use resolved-locale to test
the results of locale fallback behavior.

name: concat
desc:
Returns a string consisting of the concatenation of the inputs. Each
input is converted to a string as if by to-string.

name: cos
desc: Returns the cosine of the input.

name: divide
desc:
Returns the result of floating point division of the first input by
the second.

name: downcase
desc:
Returns the input string converted to lowercase. Follows the Unicode
Default Case Conversion algorithm and the locale-insensitive case
mappings in the Unicode Character Database.

name: e
desc: Returns the mathematical constant e.

name: equal
desc:
Returns true if the input values are equal, false otherwise. The
comparison is strictly typed: values of different runtime types are
always considered unequal. Cases where the types are known to be
different at parse time are considered invalid and will produce a
parse error. Accepts an optional collator argument to control
locale-dependent string comparisons.

name: featureState
desc:
Retrieves a property value from the current feature's state. Returns
null if the requested property is not present on the feature's state.
A feature's state is not part of the GeoJSON or vector tile data, and
must be set programmatically on each feature. Features are identified
by their id attribute, which must be an integer or a string that can
be cast to an integer. Note that "feature-state" can only be used
with paint properties that support data-driven styling.

name: floor
desc: Returns the largest integer that is less than or equal to the input.

name: format
desc:
Returns formatted text containing annotations for use in
mixed-format text-field entries. For a text-field entries of a
string type, following option object's properties are supported: If
set, the text-font value overrides the font specified by the root
layout properties. If set, the font-scale value specifies a scaling
factor relative to the text-size specified in the root layout
properties. If set, the text-color value overrides the color
specified by the root paint properties for this layer.

name: geometryType
desc:
Gets the feature's geometry type: Point, MultiPoint, LineString,
MultiLineString, Polygon, MultiPolygon.

name: get
desc:
Retrieves a property value from the current feature's properties, or
from another object if a second argument is provided. Returns null if
the requested property is missing.

name: has
desc:
Tests for the presence of an property value in the current feature's
properties, or from another object if a second argument is provided.

name: heatmapDensity
desc:
Gets the kernel density estimation of a pixel in a heatmap layer,
which is a relative measure of how many data points are crowded around
a particular pixel. Can only be used in the heatmap-color property.

name: id
desc: Gets the feature's id, if it has one.

name: image
desc:
Returns an image type for use in icon-image, *-pattern entries
and as a section in the format expression. If set, the image
argument will check that the requested image exists in the style and
will return either the resolved image name or null, depending on
whether or not the image is currently in the style. This validation
process is synchronous and requires the image to have been added to
the style before requesting it in the image argument.

name: inExpression
desc:
Determines whether an item exists in an array or a substring exists in
a string.

name: interpolate
desc:
Produces continuous, smooth results by interpolating between pairs of
input and output values ("stops"). The input may be any numeric
expression (e.g., ["get", "population"]). Stop inputs must be
numeric literals in strictly ascending order. The output type must be
number, array<number>, or color.Interpolation types:-
["linear"]: interpolates linearly between the pair of stops just
less than and just greater than the input.- ["exponential", base]:
interpolates exponentially between the stops just less than and just
greater than the input. base controls the rate at which the output
increases: higher values make the output increase more towards the
high end of the range. With values close to 1 the output increases
linearly.- ["cubic-bezier", x1, y1, x2, y2]: interpolates using the
cubic bezier curve defined by the given control points.

name: interpolateHcl
desc:
Produces continuous, smooth results by interpolating between pairs of
input and output values ("stops"). Works like interpolate, but the
output type must be color, and the interpolation is performed in the
Hue-Chroma-Luminance color space.

name: interpolateLab
desc:
Produces continuous, smooth results by interpolating between pairs of
input and output values ("stops"). Works like interpolate, but the
output type must be color, and the interpolation is performed in the
CIELAB color space.

name: isSupportedScript
desc:
Returns true if the input string is expected to render legibly.
Returns false if the input string contains sections that cannot be
rendered without potential loss of meaning (e.g. Indic scripts that
require complex text shaping, or right-to-left scripts if the the
mapbox-gl-rtl-text plugin is not in use in Mapbox GL JS).

name: larger
desc:
Returns true if the first input is strictly greater than the second,
false otherwise. The arguments are required to be either both
strings or both numbers; if during evaluation they are not, expression
evaluation produces an error. Cases where this constraint is known not
to hold at parse time are considered in valid and will produce a parse
error. Accepts an optional collator argument to control
locale-dependent string comparisons.

name: largerOrEqual
desc:
Returns true if the first input is greater than or equal to the
second, false otherwise. The arguments are required to be either
both strings or both numbers; if during evaluation they are not,
expression evaluation produces an error. Cases where this constraint
is known not to hold at parse time are considered in valid and will
produce a parse error. Accepts an optional collator argument to
control locale-dependent string comparisons.

name: length
desc: Gets the length of an array or string.

name: let
desc:
Binds expressions to named variables, which can then be referenced in
the result expression using "var", "variable_name".

name: lineProgress
desc:
Gets the progress along a gradient line. Can only be used in the
line-gradient property.

name: literal
desc: Provides a literal array or object value.

name: ln
desc: Returns the natural logarithm of the input.

name: ln2
desc: Returns mathematical constant ln(2).

name: log2
desc: Returns the base-two logarithm of the input.

name: log10
desc: Returns the base-ten logarithm of the input.

name: match
desc:
Selects the output whose label value matches the input value, or the
fallback value if no match is found. The input can be any expression
(e.g. ["get", "building_type"]). Each label must be either:

name: max
desc: Returns the maximum value of the inputs.

name: min
desc: Returns the minimum value of the inputs.

name: minus
desc:
For two inputs, returns the result of subtracting the second input
from the first. For a single input, returns the result of subtracting
it from 0.

name: multiply
desc: Returns the product of the inputs.

name: not
desc:
Logical negation. Returns true if the input is false, and false
if the input is true.

name: notEqual
desc:
Returns true if the input values are not equal, false otherwise.
The comparison is strictly typed: values of different runtime types
are always considered unequal. Cases where the types are known to be
different at parse time are considered invalid and will produce a
parse error. Accepts an optional collator argument to control
locale-dependent string comparisons.

name: number
desc:
Asserts that the input value is a number. If multiple values are
provided, each one is evaluated in order until a number is obtained.
If none of the inputs are numbers, the expression is an error.

name: numberFormat
desc:
Converts the input number into a string representation using the
providing formatting rules. If set, the locale argument specifies
the locale to use, as a BCP 47 language tag. If set, the currency
argument specifies an ISO 4217 code to use for currency-style
formatting. If set, the min-fraction-digits and
max-fraction-digits arguments specify the minimum and maximum number
of fractional digits to include.

name: object
desc:
Asserts that the input value is an object. If multiple values are
provided, each one is evaluated in order until an object is obtained.
If none of the inputs are objects, the expression is an error.

name: pi
desc: Returns the mathematical constant pi.

name: plus
desc: Returns the sum of the inputs.

name: precent
desc:
Returns the remainder after integer division of the first input by the
second.

name: properties
desc:
Gets the feature properties object.  Note that in some cases, it may
be more efficient to use "get", "property_name" directly.

name: resolvedLocale
desc:
Returns the IETF language tag of the locale being used by the provided
collator. This can be used to determine the default system locale,
or to determine if a requested locale was successfully loaded.

name: rgb
desc:
Creates a color value from red, green, and blue components, which must
range between 0 and 255, and an alpha component of 1. If any component
is out of range, the expression is an error.

name: rgba
desc:
Creates a color value from red, green, blue components, which must
range between 0 and 255, and an alpha component which must range
between 0 and 1. If any component is out of range, the expression is
an error.

name: round
desc:
Rounds the input to the nearest integer. Halfway values are rounded
away from zero. For example, ["round", -1.5] evaluates to -2.

name: sin
desc: Returns the sine of the input.

name: smaller
desc:
Returns true if the first input is strictly less than the second,
false otherwise. The arguments are required to be either both
strings or both numbers; if during evaluation they are not, expression
evaluation produces an error. Cases where this constraint is known not
to hold at parse time are considered in valid and will produce a parse
error. Accepts an optional collator argument to control
locale-dependent string comparisons.

name: smallerOrEqual
desc:
Returns true if the first input is less than or equal to the second,
false otherwise. The arguments are required to be either both
strings or both numbers; if during evaluation they are not, expression
evaluation produces an error. Cases where this constraint is known not
to hold at parse time are considered in valid and will produce a parse
error. Accepts an optional collator argument to control
locale-dependent string comparisons.

name: sqrt
desc: Returns the square root of the input.

name: step
desc:
Produces discrete, stepped results by evaluating a piecewise-constant
function defined by pairs of input and output values ("stops"). The
input may be any numeric expression (e.g., ["get", "population"]).
Stop inputs must be numeric literals in strictly ascending order.
Returns the output value of the stop just less than the input, or the
first output if the input is less than the first stop.

name: string
desc:
Asserts that the input value is a string. If multiple values are
provided, each one is evaluated in order until a string is obtained.
If none of the inputs are strings, the expression is an error.

name: tan
desc: Returns the tangent of the input.

name: toBoolean
desc:
Converts the input value to a boolean. The result is false when then
input is an empty string, 0, false, null, or NaN; otherwise it
is true.

name: toColor
desc:
Converts the input value to a color. If multiple values are provided,
each one is evaluated in order until the first successful conversion
is obtained. If none of the inputs can be converted, the expression is
an error.

name: toNumber
desc:
Converts the input value to a number, if possible. If the input is
null or false, the result is 0. If the input is true, the result
is 1. If the input is a string, it is converted to a number as
specified by the "ToNumber Applied to the String Type"
algorithm
of the ECMAScript Language Specification. If multiple values are
provided, each one is evaluated in order until the first successful
conversion is obtained. If none of the inputs can be converted, the
expression is an error.

name: toRgba
desc:
Returns a four-element array containing the input color's red, green,
blue, and alpha components, in that order.

name: toStringExpression
desc:
Converts the input value to a string. If the input is null, the
result is "". If the input is a boolean, the result is "true" or
"false". If the input is a number, it is converted to a string as
specified by the "NumberToString"
algorithm
of the ECMAScript Language Specification. If the input is a color, it
is converted to a string of the form "rgba(r,g,b,a)", where r,
g, and b are numerals ranging from 0 to 255, and a ranges from 0
to 1. Otherwise, the input is converted to a string in the format
specified by the
JSON.stringify
function of the ECMAScript Language Specification.

name: typeof
desc: Returns a string describing the type of the given value.

name: upcase
desc:
Returns the input string converted to uppercase. Follows the Unicode
Default Case Conversion algorithm and the locale-insensitive case
mappings in the Unicode Character Database.

name: varExpression
desc: References variable bound using "let".

name: xor
desc:
Returns the result of raising the first input to the power specified
by the second.

name: zoom
desc:
Gets the current zoom level.  Note that in style layout and paint
properties, "zoom" may only appear as the input to a top-level
"step" or "interpolate" expression.

name: fillAntialias
desc: Whether or not the fill should be antialiased.

name: fillColor
desc:
The color of the filled part of this layer. This color can be
specified as rgba with an alpha component and the color's opacity
will not affect the opacity of the 1px stroke, if it is used.

name: fillOpacity
desc:
The opacity of the entire fill layer. In contrast to the fill-color,
this value will also affect the 1px stroke around the fill, if the
stroke is used.

name: fillOutlineColor
desc:
The outline color of the fill. Matches the value of fill-color if
unspecified.

name: fillPattern
desc:
Name of image in sprite to use for drawing image fills. For seamless
patterns, image width and height must be a factor of two (2, 4, 8,
..., 512). Note that zoom-dependent expressions will be evaluated only
at integer zoom levels.

name: fillSortKey
desc:
Sorts features in ascending order based on this value. Features with a
higher sort key will appear above features with a lower sort key.

name: fillTranslate
desc:
The geometry's offset. Values are x, y where negatives indicate left
and up, respectively.

name: fillTranslateAnchor
desc: Controls the frame of reference for fill-translate.

name: visibility
desc: Whether this layer is displayed.

name: allLayerProperties
desc: implemented to define the layer properties

name: hillshadeAccentColor
desc:
The shading color used to accentuate rugged terrain like sharp cliffs
and gorges.

name: hillshadeExaggeration
desc: Intensity of the hillshade

name: hillshadeHighlightColor
desc: The shading color of areas that faces towards the light source.

name: hillshadeIlluminationAnchor
desc: Direction of light source when map is rotated.

name: hillshadeIlluminationDirection
desc:
The direction of the light source used to generate the hillshading
with 0 as the top of the viewport if hillshade-illumination-anchor
is set to viewport and due north if hillshade-illumination-anchor
is set to map.

name: hillshadeShadowColor
desc: The shading color of areas that face away from the light source.

name: visibility
desc: Whether this layer is displayed.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: lineBlur
desc: Blur applied to the line, in pixels.

name: lineCap
desc: The display of line endings.

name: lineColor
desc: The color with which the line will be drawn.

name: lineDasharray
desc:
Specifies the lengths of the alternating dashes and gaps that form the
dash pattern. The lengths are later scaled by the line width. To
convert a dash length to pixels, multiply the length by the current
line width. Note that GeoJSON sources with lineMetrics: true
specified won't render dashed lines to the expected scale. Also note
that zoom-dependent expressions will be evaluated only at integer zoom
levels.

name: lineGapWidth
desc:
Draws a line casing outside of a line's actual path. Value indicates
the width of the inner gap.

name: lineGradient
desc:
Defines a gradient with which to color a line feature. Can only be
used with GeoJSON sources that specify "lineMetrics": true.

name: lineJoin
desc: The display of lines when joining.

name: lineMiterLimit
desc:
Used to automatically convert miter joins to bevel joins for sharp
angles.

name: lineOffset
desc:
The line's offset. For linear features, a positive value offsets the
line to the right, relative to the direction of the line, and a
negative value to the left. For polygon features, a positive value
results in an inset, and a negative value results in an outset.

name: lineOpacity
desc: The opacity at which the line will be drawn.

name: linePattern
desc:
Name of image in sprite to use for drawing image lines. For seamless
patterns, image width must be a factor of two (2, 4, 8, ..., 512).
Note that zoom-dependent expressions will be evaluated only at integer
zoom levels.

name: lineRoundLimit
desc:
Used to automatically convert round joins to miter joins for shallow
angles.

name: lineSortKey
desc:
Sorts features in ascending order based on this value. Features with a
higher sort key will appear above features with a lower sort key.

name: lineTranslate
desc:
The geometry's offset. Values are x, y where negatives indicate left
and up, respectively.

name: lineTranslateAnchor
desc: Controls the frame of reference for line-translate.

name: lineWidth
desc: Stroke thickness.

name: visibility
desc: Whether this layer is displayed.

name: allLayerProperties
desc: implemented to define the layer properties

name: OfflineRegion
desc: Description of a downloaded region including its identifier.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: OfflineRegionDefinition
desc:
Description of region to be downloaded. Identifier will be generated when
the download is initiated.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: rasterBrightnessMax
desc:
Increase or reduce the brightness of the image. The value is the
maximum brightness.

name: rasterBrightnessMin
desc:
Increase or reduce the brightness of the image. The value is the
minimum brightness.

name: rasterContrast
desc: Increase or reduce the contrast of the image.

name: rasterFadeDuration
desc: Fade duration when a new tile is added.

name: rasterHueRotate
desc: Rotates hues around the color wheel.

name: rasterOpacity
desc: The opacity at which the image will be drawn.

name: rasterResampling
desc:
The resampling/interpolation method to use for overscaling, also known
as texture magnification filter

name: rasterSaturation
desc: Increase or reduce the saturation of the image.

name: visibility
desc: Whether this layer is displayed.

name: iconAllowOverlap
desc:
If true, the icon will be visible even if it collides with other
previously drawn symbols.

name: iconAnchor
desc: Part of the icon placed closest to the anchor.

name: iconColor
desc: The color of the icon. This can only be used with sdf icons.

name: iconHaloBlur
desc: Fade out the halo towards the outside.

name: iconHaloColor
desc:
The color of the icon's halo. Icon halos can only be used with SDF
icons.

name: iconHaloWidth
desc: Distance of halo to the icon outline.

name: iconIgnorePlacement
desc:
If true, other symbols can be visible even if they collide with the
icon.

name: iconImage
desc: Name of image in sprite to use for drawing an image background.

name: iconKeepUpright
desc:
If true, the icon may be flipped to prevent it from being rendered
upside-down.

name: iconOffset
desc:
Offset distance of icon from its anchor. Positive values indicate
right and down, while negative values indicate left and up. Each
component is multiplied by the value of icon-size to obtain the
final offset in pixels. When combined with icon-rotate the offset
will be as if the rotated direction was up.

name: iconOpacity
desc: The opacity at which the icon will be drawn.

name: iconOptional
desc:
If true, text will display without their corresponding icons when the
icon collides with other symbols and the text does not.

name: iconPadding
desc:
Size of the additional area around the icon bounding box used for
detecting symbol collisions.

name: iconPitchAlignment
desc: Orientation of icon when map is pitched.

name: iconRotate
desc: Rotates the icon clockwise.

name: iconRotationAlignment
desc:
In combination with symbol-placement, determines the rotation
behavior of icons.

name: iconSize
desc:
Scales the original size of the icon by the provided factor. The new
pixel size of the image will be the original pixel size multiplied by
icon-size. 1 is the original size; 3 triples the size of the image.

name: iconTextFit
desc: Scales the icon to fit around the associated text.

name: iconTextFitPadding
desc:
Size of the additional area added to dimensions determined by
icon-text-fit, in clockwise order: top, right, bottom, left.

name: iconTranslate
desc:
Distance that the icon's anchor is moved from its original placement.
Positive values indicate right and down, while negative values
indicate left and up.

name: iconTranslateAnchor
desc: Controls the frame of reference for icon-translate.

name: symbolAvoidEdges
desc:
If true, the symbols will not cross tile edges to avoid mutual
collisions. Recommended in layers that don't have enough padding in
the vector tile to prevent collisions, or if it is a point symbol
layer placed after a line symbol layer. When using a client that
supports global collision detection, like Mapbox GL JS version 0.42.0
or greater, enabling this property is not needed to prevent clipped
labels at tile boundaries.

name: symbolPlacement
desc: Label placement relative to its geometry.

name: symbolSortKey
desc:
Sorts features in ascending order based on this value. Features with
lower sort keys are drawn and placed first.  When icon-allow-overlap
or text-allow-overlap is false, features with a lower sort key
will have priority during placement. When icon-allow-overlap or
text-allow-overlap is set to true, features with a higher sort key
will overlap over features with a lower sort key.

name: symbolSpacing
desc: Distance between two symbol anchors.

name: symbolZOrder
desc:
Controls the order in which overlapping symbols in the same layer are
rendered

name: textAllowOverlap
desc:
If true, the text will be visible even if it collides with other
previously drawn symbols.

name: textAnchor
desc: Part of the text placed closest to the anchor.

name: textColor
desc: The color with which the text will be drawn.

name: textField
desc:
Value to use for a text label. If a plain string is provided, it
will be treated as a formatted with default/inherited formatting
options.

name: textFont
desc: Font stack to use for displaying text.

name: textHaloBlur
desc: The halo's fadeout distance towards the outside.

name: textHaloColor
desc:
The color of the text's halo, which helps it stand out from
backgrounds.

name: textHaloWidth
desc:
Distance of halo to the font outline. Max text halo width is 1/4 of
the font-size.

name: textIgnorePlacement
desc:
If true, other symbols can be visible even if they collide with the
text.

name: textJustify
desc: Text justification options.

name: textKeepUpright
desc:
If true, the text may be flipped vertically to prevent it from being
rendered upside-down.

name: textLetterSpacing
desc: Text tracking amount.

name: textLineHeight
desc: Text leading value for multi-line text.

name: textMaxAngle
desc: Maximum angle change between adjacent characters.

name: textMaxWidth
desc: The maximum line width for text wrapping.

name: textOffset
desc:
Offset distance of text from its anchor. Positive values indicate
right and down, while negative values indicate left and up. If used
with text-variable-anchor, input values will be taken as absolute
values. Offsets along the x- and y-axis will be applied automatically
based on the anchor position.

name: textOpacity
desc: The opacity at which the text will be drawn.

name: textOptional
desc:
If true, icons will display without their corresponding text when the
text collides with other symbols and the icon does not.

name: textPadding
desc:
Size of the additional area around the text bounding box used for
detecting symbol collisions.

name: textPitchAlignment
desc: Orientation of text when map is pitched.

name: textRadialOffset
desc:
Radial offset of text, in the direction of the symbol's anchor. Useful
in combination with text-variable-anchor, which defaults to using
the two-dimensional text-offset if present.

name: textRotate
desc: Rotates the text clockwise.

name: textRotationAlignment
desc:
In combination with symbol-placement, determines the rotation
behavior of the individual glyphs forming the text.

name: textSize
desc: Font size.

name: textTransform
desc:
Specifies how to capitalize text, similar to the CSS text-transform
property.

name: textTranslate
desc:
Distance that the text's anchor is moved from its original placement.
Positive values indicate right and down, while negative values
indicate left and up.

name: textTranslateAnchor
desc: Controls the frame of reference for text-translate.

name: textVariableAnchor
desc:
To increase the chance of placing high-priority labels on the map, you
can provide an array of text-anchor locations: the renderer will
attempt to place the label at each location, in order, before moving
onto the next label. Use text-justify: auto to choose justification
based on anchor position. To apply an offset, use the
text-radial-offset or the two-dimensional text-offset.

name: textWritingMode
desc:
The property allows control over a symbol's orientation. Note that the
property values act as a hint, so that a symbol whose language doesn’t
support the provided orientation will be laid out in its natural
orientation. Example: English point symbol will be rendered
horizontally even if array value contains single 'vertical' enum
value. The order of elements in an array define priority order for the
placement of an orientation variant.

name: visibility
desc: Whether this layer is displayed.

name: allLayerProperties
desc: implemented to define the layer properties

name: setIconAllowOverlap
desc: For more information on what this does, see https://docs.mapbox.com/help/troubleshooting/optimize-map-label-placement/#label-collision

name: setIconIgnorePlacement
desc: For more information on what this does, see https://docs.mapbox.com/help/troubleshooting/optimize-map-label-placement/#label-collision

name: setTextAllowOverlap
desc: For more information on what this does, see https://docs.mapbox.com/help/troubleshooting/optimize-map-label-placement/#label-collision

name: setTextIgnorePlacement
desc: For more information on what this does, see https://docs.mapbox.com/help/troubleshooting/optimize-map-label-placement/#label-collision

name: annotationConsumeTapEvents
desc: Defines the layer order of click annotations

name: annotationOrder
desc: Defines the layer order of annotations displayed on map

name: attributionButtonMargins
desc:
Set the layout margins for the Mapbox Attribution Buttons. If you set this
value, you may also want to set attributionButtonPosition to harmonize
the layout between iOS and Android, since the underlying frameworks have
different defaults.

name: attributionButtonPosition
desc: Set the position for the Mapbox Attribution Button

name: cameraTargetBounds
desc: Geographical bounding box for the camera target.

name: compassEnabled
desc: True if the map should show a compass when rotated.

name: compassViewMargins
desc: Set the layout margins for the Mapbox Compass

name: compassViewPosition
desc: Set the position for the Mapbox Compass

name: createState
desc: Creates the mutable state for this widget at a given location in the tree.

name: doubleClickZoomEnabled
desc:
Set to true to forcefully disable/enable if map should respond to double
click to zoom.

name: dragEnabled
desc: True if drag functionality should be enabled.

name: gestureRecognizers
desc: Which gestures should be consumed by the map.

name: initialCameraPosition
desc: The initial position of the map's camera.

name: logoViewMargins
desc: Set the layout margins for the Mapbox Logo

name: minMaxZoomPreference
desc: Preferred bounds for the camera zoom level.

name: myLocationEnabled
desc: True if a "My Location" layer should be shown on the map.

name: myLocationRenderMode
desc:
Specifies if and how the user's heading/bearing is rendered in the user location indicator.
See the documentation of MyLocationRenderMode for details.
If this is set to a value other than MyLocationRenderMode.NORMAL, myLocationEnabled needs to be true.

name: myLocationTrackingMode
desc:
The mode used to let the map's camera follow the device's physical location.
myLocationEnabled needs to be true for values other than MyLocationTrackingMode.None to work.

name: onCameraTrackingChanged
desc: Called when the location tracking mode changes

name: onCameraTrackingDismissed
desc: Called when the map's camera no longer follows the physical device location, e.g. because the user moved the map

name: onMapCreated
desc: Please note: you should only add annotations (e.g. symbols or circles) after onStyleLoadedCallback has been called.

name: onMapIdle
desc:
Called when map view is entering an idle state, and no more drawing will
be necessary until new data is loaded or there is some interaction with
the map.

name: onStyleLoadedCallback
desc:
Called when the map style has been successfully loaded and the annotation managers have been enabled.
Please note: you should only add annotations (e.g. symbols or circles) after this callback has been called.

name: onUserLocationUpdated
desc:
While the myLocationEnabled property is set to true, this method is
called whenever a new location update is received by the map view.

name: rotateGesturesEnabled
desc: True if the map view should respond to rotate gestures.

name: scrollGesturesEnabled
desc: True if the map view should respond to scroll gestures.

name: styleString
desc:
Style URL or Style JSON
Can be a MapboxStyle constant, any Mapbox Style URL,
or a StyleJSON (https://docs.mapbox.com/mapbox-gl-js/style-spec/)

name: tiltGesturesEnabled
desc: True if the map view should respond to tilt gestures.

name: trackCameraPosition
desc: True if you want to be notified of map camera movements by the TrackasiaMapController. Default is false.

name: useHybridComposition
desc:
Set TrackasiaMap.useHybridComposition to false in order use Virtual-Display
(better for Android 9 and below but may result in errors on Android 12)
or leave it true (default) to use Hybrid composition (Slower on Android 9 and below).

name: zoomGesturesEnabled
desc: True if the map view should respond to zoom gestures.

name: TrackasiaMapController
desc: Controller for a single TrackasiaMap instance running on the host platform.

name: addCircle
desc: Adds a circle to the map, configured using the specified custom options.

name: addCircleLayer
desc: Add a circle layer to the map with the given properties

name: addCircles
desc:
Adds multiple circles to the map, configured using the specified custom
options.

name: addFill
desc: Adds a fill to the map, configured using the specified custom options.

name: addFillLayer
desc: Add a fill layer to the map with the given properties

name: addFills
desc:
Adds multiple fills to the map, configured using the specified custom
options.

name: addGeoJsonSource
desc: Adds a new geojson source

name: addHillshadeLayer
desc: Add a hillshade layer to the map with the given properties

name: addImage
desc: Adds an image to the style currently displayed in the map, so that it can later be referred to by the provided name.

name: addImageLayer
desc: Adds a Mapbox image layer to the map's style at render time.

name: addImageLayerBelow
desc: Adds a Mapbox image layer below the layer provided with belowLayerId to the map's style at render time.

name: addImageSource
desc: Adds an image source to the style currently displayed in the map, so that it can later be referred to by the provided id.

name: addLayer
desc: Add a layer to the map with the given properties

name: addLayerBelow
desc: Adds a Mapbox image layer below the layer provided with belowLayerId to the map's style at render time. Only works for image sources!

name: addLine
desc: Adds a line to the map, configured using the specified custom options.

name: addLineLayer
desc: Add a line layer to the map with the given properties

name: addLines
desc: Adds multiple lines to the map, configured using the specified custom options.

name: addRasterLayer
desc: Add a raster layer to the map with the given properties

name: addSource
desc: Add a new source to the map

name: addSymbol
desc: Adds a symbol to the map, configured using the specified custom options.

name: addSymbolLayer
desc: Add a symbol layer to the map with the given properties

name: addSymbols
desc:
Adds multiple symbols to the map, configured using the specified custom
options.

name: animateCamera
desc: Starts an animated change of the map camera position.

name: cameraPosition
desc:
Returns the most recent camera position reported by the platform side.
Will be null, if TrackasiaMap.trackCameraPosition is false.

name: circles
desc: The current set of circles on this map.

name: clearCircles
desc: Removes all circles from the map.

name: clearFills
desc: Removes all fill from the map.

name: clearLines
desc: Removes all lines from the map.

name: clearSymbols
desc: Removes all symbols from the map.

name: dispose
desc:
Discards any resources used by the object. After this is called, the
object is not in a usable state and should be discarded (calls to
addListener will throw after the object is disposed).

name: fills
desc: The current set of fills on this map.

name: forceResizeWebMap
desc: Triggers a hard map resize event on web and does not check if it is required or not.

name: getCircleLatLng
desc:
Retrieves the current position of the circle.
This may be different from the value of circle.options.geometry if the circle is draggable.
In that case this method provides the circle's actual position, and circle.options.geometry the last programmatically set position.

name: getLineLatLngs
desc:
Retrieves the current position of the line.
This may be different from the value of line.options.geometry if the line is draggable.
In that case this method provides the line's actual position, and line.options.geometry the last programmatically set position.

name: getMetersPerPixelAtLatitude
desc:
Returns the distance spanned by one pixel at the specified latitude and current zoom level.
The distance between pixels decreases as the latitude approaches the poles. This relationship parallels the relationship between longitudinal coordinates at different latitudes.

name: getSourceIds
desc: Retrieve every source ids of the map as a String list, including the ones added internally

name: getSymbolLatLng
desc:
Retrieves the current position of the symbol.
This may be different from the value of symbol.options.geometry if the symbol is draggable.
In that case this method provides the symbol's actual position, and symbol.options.geometry the last programmatically set position.

name: getTelemetryEnabled
desc: Retrieves whether collection of anonymized telemetry data is enabled.

name: getVisibleRegion
desc: This method returns the boundaries of the region currently displayed in the map.

name: isCameraMoving
desc: True if the map camera is currently moving.

name: lines
desc: The current set of lines on this map.

name: matchMapLanguageWithDeviceDefault
desc: Updates the language of the map labels to match the device's language.

name: moveCamera
desc:
Instantaneously re-position the camera.
Note: moveCamera() quickly moves the camera, which can be visually jarring for a user. Strongly consider using the animateCamera() methods instead because it's less abrupt.

name: onCircleTapped
desc: Callbacks to receive tap events for symbols placed on this map.

name: onFeatureTapped
desc: Callbacks to receive tap events for features (geojson layer) placed on this map.

name: onFillTapped
desc: Callbacks to receive tap events for fills placed on this map.

name: onInfoWindowTapped
desc: Callbacks to receive tap events for info windows on symbols

name: onLineTapped
desc: Callbacks to receive tap events for lines placed on this map.

name: onSymbolTapped
desc: Callbacks to receive tap events for symbols placed on this map.

name: queryRenderedFeatures
desc: Query rendered features at a point in screen cooridnates

name: queryRenderedFeaturesInRect
desc: Query rendered features in a Rect in screen coordinates

name: querySourceFeatures
desc:
Query rendered features at a point in screen coordinates
Note: On web, this will probably only work for GeoJson source, not for vector tiles

name: removeCircle
desc:
Removes the specified circle from the map. The circle must be a current
member of the circles set.

name: removeCircles
desc:
Removes the specified circles from the map. The circles must be current
members of the circles set.

name: removeFill
desc:
Removes the specified fill from the map. The fill must be a current
member of the fills set.

name: removeFills
desc:
Removes the specified fills from the map. The fills must be current
members of the fills set.

name: removeImageSource
desc: Removes previously added image source by id

name: removeLayer
desc: Removes a Mapbox style layer

name: removeLine
desc:
Removes the specified line from the map. The line must be a current
member of the lines set.

name: removeLines
desc:
Removes the specified lines from the map. The lines must be current
members of the lines set.

name: removeSource
desc: Removes previously added source by id

name: removeSymbol
desc:
Removes the specified symbol from the map. The symbol must be a current
member of the symbols set.

name: removeSymbols
desc:
Removes the specified symbols from the map. The symbols must be current
members of the symbols set.

name: requestMyLocationLatLng
desc: Get last my location

name: resizeWebMap
desc: Triggers a resize event for the map on web (ignored on Android or iOS).

name: setGeoJsonFeature
desc: Sets new geojson data to and existing source

name: setGeoJsonSource
desc: Sets new geojson data to and existing source

name: setMapLanguage
desc:
Updates the language of the map labels to match the specified language.
Supported language strings are available here: https://github.com/mapbox/mapbox-plugins-android/blob/e29c18d25098eb023a831796ff807e30d8207c36/plugin-localization/src/main/java/com.trackasia.android.plugins/localization/MapLocale.java#L39-L87
Attention: This may only be called after onStyleLoaded() has been invoked.

name: setSymbolIconAllowOverlap
desc: For more information on what this does, see https://docs.mapbox.com/help/troubleshooting/optimize-map-label-placement/#label-collision

name: setSymbolIconIgnorePlacement
desc: For more information on what this does, see https://docs.mapbox.com/help/troubleshooting/optimize-map-label-placement/#label-collision

name: setSymbolTextAllowOverlap
desc: For more information on what this does, see https://docs.mapbox.com/help/troubleshooting/optimize-map-label-placement/#label-collision

name: setSymbolTextIgnorePlacement
desc: For more information on what this does, see https://docs.mapbox.com/help/troubleshooting/optimize-map-label-placement/#label-collision

name: setTelemetryEnabled
desc: Enables or disables the collection of anonymized telemetry data.

name: symbols
desc: The current set of symbols on this map.

name: toLatLng
desc: Returns the geographic location (as LatLng) that corresponds to a point on the screen. The screen location is specified in screen pixels (not display pixels) relative to the top left of the map (not the top left of the whole screen).

name: toScreenLocation
desc: Returns the point on the screen that corresponds to a geographical coordinate (latLng). The screen location is in screen pixels (not display pixels) relative to the top left of the map (not of the whole screen)

name: updateCircle
desc:
Updates the specified circle with the given changes. The circle must
be a current member of the circles set.

name: updateContentInsets
desc:
Updates the distance from the edges of the map view’s frame to the edges
of the map view’s logical viewport, optionally animating the change.

name: updateFill
desc:
Updates the specified fill with the given changes. The fill must
be a current member of the fills set.

name: updateLine
desc:
Updates the specified line with the given changes. The line must
be a current member of the lines set.‚

name: updateMyLocationTrackingMode
desc: Updates user location tracking mode.

name: updateSymbol
desc:
Updates the specified symbol with the given changes. The symbol must
be a current member of the symbols set.

name: installOfflineMapTiles
desc:
Copy tiles db file passed in to the tiles cache directory (sideloaded) to
make tiles available offline.
